      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "supra.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of the lowest of them.—Rather, of all orders, or promiscuously. (Comp. 1Kings 12:31.) This is another indication that it was Jeroboam’s mode of worship which was now restored.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Of the lowest of them.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "of all orders,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " or ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "promiscuously.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Kings 12:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) This is another indication that it was ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Jeroboam’s",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " mode of worship which was now restored.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which sacrificed.—Heb., and they used to do. The verb do is used in the sense of sacra facere, just like the Greek - ποιεῗν ἔρδειν ρέζειν.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Which sacrificed.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and they used to do.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " The verb ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "do",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " is used in the sense of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "sacra facere,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " just like the Greek ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "-",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "greekheb",
            "text": "ποιεῗν ἔρδειν ρέζειν",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Priests of the high places.—Rather, bāmāh-priests (omit the). Bamah-priests are opposed to the priests of Jehovah’s Temple.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Priests of the high places.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "bāmāh-priests",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (omit ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Bamah-priests are opposed to the priests of Jehovah’s Temple.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
